commits.author: Otis Gospodnetic
commits.sourceNew:
/** * Handle significant character data. *

Please note that the contents of the array will be * accurate only for the duration of this handler: if you need to * use them elsewhere, you should make your own copy, possible * by constructing a string:

* 
    * String data = new String(ch, start, length);
    *
* @param ch An array of characters. * @param start The starting position in the array. * @param length The number of characters to use in the array. * @exception java.lang.Exception You may throw any exception. */ public void characters (char ch[], int start, int length) throws Exception;
